Iraq inquiry to recall Blair for questioning
In the UK, Tony Blair will be recalled to give evidence to the Iraq inquiry.
Sir John Chilcot has confirmed the former British Prime Minister will be among several witnesses who will be asked to give more detail.
The former British Foreign Secretary Jack Straw is also due to return.
The inquiry - which is looking into the 2003 invasion of Iraq and the aftermath of the war - will resume in Westminster on January 18.